RugbySim is a fork that replaces the football match logic, match physics,
AI behaviours, set-piece handling, and visual assets (pitch overlay, ball
mesh, goalposts, kits, and in-game radar) with rugby-union equivalents,
while retaining the underlying rendering + reinforcement-learning
scaffolding of the upstream project.

See UPSTREAM.md for a summary of the fork's intent and the relationship to
the upstream project.
